dn/shop/files/UMI30NE3SSP-28_112.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">ILVE USA Brochure.pdf</a></li><li><i></i> <a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/UMI30NE3SSP-28_6905.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">ILVE USA Majestic Order Form.pdf</a></li><li><i></i> <a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/UMI30NE3SSP-28_7630.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">ILVE-Warranty.pdf</a></li><li><i></i> <a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/UMI30NE3SSP-28_114.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Majestic II Manual.pdf</a></li><li><i></i> <a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/UMI30NE3SSP-28_7441.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Majestic-II-Overview.pdf</a></li><li><i></i> <a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/UMI30NE3SSP-28_7442.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Majestic-II-Range-Specs.pdf</a></li><li><i></i> <a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/UMI30NE3SSP-28_7443.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Majestic-II-UM30N-Spec-Sheet.pdf</a></li></ul> </div> </div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_accessories\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tab mod-last\\\" data-slug=\\\"accessories\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tab_accessories\\\" role=\\\"tab\\\" tabindex=\\\"-1\\\"> <span class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtext\\\">Accessories</span> </span></h3> <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_accessories\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_accessories\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"> <div><div><div><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/A41802_p20023-1.png\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE A/418/02 Pizza Stone For Maxi Oven</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>182.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+am476\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/AM476_p20029.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE AM4-76 30 inch Stainless Steel Backsplash</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>265.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+ea2633006000008\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/EA2633006000008_p16230-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE EA2633006000008 Stainless Steel Wire Grid Grates For Stacking on Maxi Oven Drip Tray</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>84.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+ea4053004030006\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/EA4053004030006_p16234-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE EA4053004030006 Drip Pan For Maxi Oven</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>140.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+kgset001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/KGSET001_p20076.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE KGSET001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Stainless Steel\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Copper\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Triple Glass Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 30 inch Majestic II Induction Range with 4 Elements (White / Burnished / Triple Glass Door) - UMI30NE3WHB\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMI30NE3WHB\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840-3.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_189645-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_189646-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_168539-4.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_14940-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_10712-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_168977-4.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_10713-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_10714-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3WHB_p12840_10715-3.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"7990.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202193795\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>The Majestic 30\\\" induction range combines cutting-edge technology with traditional Italian design. This range has four precise and effective element zones, four cu sq. total oven capacity, 4.3-inch full touch oven control display, and easily cleaned enamel oven cavity.</p><p>Stocked</p><div><p><strong>Magnificent</strong></p><p>The eye-catching range cooker that makes your kitchen distinctive.</p><p></p><p>Majestic is a daring, expert representation of the ideal range cooker, combining beauty and functionality. A free-standing statement piece with a style that features rounded lines, expertly crafted details, exquisite finishes, solutions, and technologies straight from the world of professional cooking that instantly takes center stage and blends into any setting.</p><p></p><p>The rounded shapes of majestic range cookers, which are crafted from pure steel with meticulously made details, make them aesthetically pleasing appliances.</p><p></p><p>They are genuine works of art, created for your home's kitchen. They come with exquisite metallic finishes and are offered in a variety of chosen colors or in RAL Classic shades upon request. They are available in a variety of sizes (from 30 to 60 inches) and provide numerous setup options.</p><p></p><ul><li>indicator of residual heat</li><li>Automatic stop timer</li><li>Bridge monitoring</li><li>Booster function</li><li>Slide controls</li><li>Child safety</li><li>4.3-inch full-touch display</li><li>Protection from liquid spills and overheating</li><li>precise electronic temperature regulation</li><li>Quick start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Product Technologies</strong></p><p></p><p>Aesthetics are important, but that's not all. To cook well and enjoyably, the best technologies are required. In order to consistently ensure the highest level of satisfaction, ILVE puts all of its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that combine optimal performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooktop (Hob) Technology</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>(Hob) Induction Cooktop</strong></p><p>Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) combine the newest technology with an elegant and sophisticated design to provide a quick, safe, and practical method of cooking. Induction offers a number of benefits, including ease of cleaning, energy conservation, safety, flexible temperature control, and cooking speed, all of which make it easier to prepare meals and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Indicator of Remaining Heat</strong></p><p>indicates that the glass is hot, so care should be taken when handling it and putting objects on it to prevent damage.</p><p></p><p><strong>Automatic Stop Timer</strong></p><p>Once the predetermined amount of time has passed, the active zone is turned off.</p><p></p><p><strong>Bridge Management</strong></p><p>This feature allows induction cooktops (hobs) to simultaneously control two adjacent zones with a single command, just like a single zone.</p><p></p><p><strong>Booster Function</strong></p><p>enables you to concentrate all of the induction cooktop's power in the designated zone to shorten boiling and cooking times.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Controls</strong></p><p>With the help of this practical \\\"touch control\\\" system, you can, for instance, change the operating temperature by moving your finger from right to left or vice versa.</p><p></p><p><strong>Child Safety</strong></p><p>The induction cooktop (hob) does not turn on by turning on the controls once this function has been set and until it is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Liquid Spill Protection and Overheating</strong></p><p>A safety device trips and stops operation if the cooktop (hob) overheats or spills liquid.</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Oven Technology</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Ovens: Magnificent Size and Performance.</strong></p><p>Any single or double combination oven you select will give you all the space you require, even for large dishes. Our 30-inch range has an oven capacity of up to 4 cubic feet.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Temperature Control</strong></p><p>The electronic control makes sure that the oven's temperature doesn't change throughout, unlike in traditional ovens.</p><p></p><p><strong>4.3\\\" Touchscreen</strong></p><p>The display's superior readability is guaranteed by TFT technology, which provides instantaneous, clear graphics for each function.</p><p></p><p><strong>User-Friendly, Comprehensive, and High Resolution TFT Display.</strong></p><p>To control all of the features of the single oven or the two ovens with a single device, just touch the large display with one finger. With a single motion and a quick glance, you can control the temperature, timer, and automatic cooking start and end programmer.</p><p></p><p><strong>Soft-Closing Door</strong></p><p>A shock absorber installed in the door hinges allows for a more gradual and silent closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Probe</strong></p><p>An indispensable tool for determining the core temperature, such as in meat cuts.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Steam</strong></p><p>You can select a drier or more moist cooking method thanks to this system, which removes the vapors from inside the cavity. You can produce a soft and juicy roast or a crispy baked dish in this manner.</p><p></p><p><strong>Temperature ranging from 85\\u00b0 to 575\\u00b0 F</strong></p><p>ILVE ovens make it simple to prepare intricate and sophisticated recipes with flawless results, from proofing to cooking, roasting to low temperature.</p><p></p><p><strong>High Density Insulation and Ventilation for Tangential Cooling</strong></p><p>prevents the kitchen and the furniture near the oven from getting too hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>For Complete Cleaning, Fold the Grill Coil</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered to more easily clean the upper portion of the cavity thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Enamel Cleaning</strong></p><p>Grease can be cleaned more easily because it does not adhere to the surface.</p><p></p><p><strong>Oven Features UOV 76 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Pizza service</li><li>Defrosting</li><li>Cooking intensively</li><li>Quick start</li><li>Cooking with lots of moisture</li><li>Cooking on a fan grill</li><li>Grill cooking with a closed door</li><li>Cooking from above</li><li>Cooking that is moist from above</li><li>Cooking from below</li><li>Cooking that is moist from below</li><li>Normal cooking that is static</li><li>Cooking that is moist and static</li><li>multiple fans cooking</li><li>multiple moist fans cooking</li><li>cooking ECO</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Pizza Party</strong></p><p>Suitable for baking pizza, as well as bread and focaccia The lower heating element serves as the primary heat source and, along with the other underpowered heating elements, produces the ideal environment for this kind of cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Defrosting</strong></p><p>Assures that all frozen food is quickly defrosted and brought to room temperature without losing its flavor or appearance.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Intensive</strong></p><p>With steam discharge, it guarantees quick and thorough cooking. Baked potatoes and vegetables, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc. are advised for a crispy outcome.</p><p></p><p><strong>Quick Start</strong></p><p>With the quick preheating function, you can quickly reach your desired temperature before selecting the cooking mode that best suits your dish. When set to a low temperature, it also functions as a quick defrosting device.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Moisture</strong></p><p>The steam block ensures rapid and thorough cooking. It is advised for moist cooking, such as chicken cacciatore, braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, etc.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking on a Fan Grill</strong></p><p>This function is especially quick and deep, and it saves a lot of energy. It can be used for a variety of foods, including game, pork chops, sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, and Roman-style gnocchi.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grill Cooking with a Closed Door</strong></p><p>Recommended for quick and deep grilling, browning, and roasting meat in general, fillet, Florentine steak, fish, and even vegetables.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking from Above</strong></p><p>It is especially good for browning and adding the last bit of color to many foods; it is the recommended function for burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Moisture from Above</strong></p><p>Ideal for browning and giving many foods a final pop of color without sacrificing their tenderness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking from the Ground Up</strong></p><p>Pastries (biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.) are best cooked using this technique to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Moist from Below</strong></p><p>This is the best cooking technique for finishing the cooking cycle while keeping the proper moisture content.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking Static Normal</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues and biscuits, baked fruit, etc. can all be cooked in this traditional electric oven function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Moist Static</strong></p><p>This increases the moisture content of typical static cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Several Fans</strong></p><p>This feature enables cooking multiple dishes at once without the smells blending. Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can be baked, saving time and electricity.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Several Moist Fans</strong></p><p>Multiple-fan cooking gains more moisture as a result.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking ECO</strong></p><p>This feature enables you to cook while using much less electricity. Braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries are just a few examples of foods that benefit from slow roasting when using the ECO function. For frozen foods, this cooking cycle is not advised.</p><p></p><p><strong>Proposition 65 in California</strong></p><p>WARNING: Cancer and Reproductive Harm</p><p><strong><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">P65Warnings.ca.gov</a></strong></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/re1Uo4qdmcc.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" p